---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const pageTitle = "About Me";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-body">
          <h1 class="title">About Me</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">Hi, I'm Roger Rajaratnam aka Sourcier</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="section">
        <div class="content">
          <p>
            Hi, I'm Roger — a software engineer, technical lead, and lifelong
            builder of things on the web.
          </p>

          <p>
            I'm currently a Technical Lead based in London, where I work on
            building scalable, user-focused applications. Over the past several
            years, I've had the opportunity to design and deliver production
            systems across fintech and consumer technology, working with modern
            web technologies such as JavaScript, TypeScript, Node.js, and React.
            My work often sits at the intersection of architecture, product
            delivery, and engineering leadership.
          </p>

          <p>
            What motivates me most about software engineering is the opportunity
            to turn ideas into real, usable products. I enjoy solving complex
            technical problems, but equally value building systems that are
            maintainable, well-tested, and understandable by the teams who work
            on them.
          </p>

          <p>
            Alongside building software, I'm passionate about helping other
            developers grow. I've spent time mentoring engineers and teaching at
            coding bootcamps, where I guide aspiring developers through the
            fundamentals of modern web development and practical engineering
            practices. Sharing knowledge and helping others break into tech has
            become one of the most rewarding parts of my career.
          </p>

          <p>
            My background includes a degree in Computer Software Engineering
            from the University of Westminster, where I built the foundations
            that led me into full-stack development and system design. Since
            then, my career has taken me through different teams and domains,
            from startups to established companies, each shaping how I approach
            engineering, collaboration, and leadership.
          </p>

          <p>
            Outside of work, I'm naturally curious about technology, systems
            thinking, and the craft of software engineering. This blog is a
            place where I share lessons learned from building software, leading
            engineering teams, and exploring the tools and ideas shaping the
            modern web.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
